"{\n    \"Title\": \"December 31, 2012 and 2011Notes to the consolidated financial statements\",\n    \"row 1\": \"(In thousands of dollars)\",\n    \"row 2\": \"9, Bank jioans and derivative instruments\",\n    \"row 3\": \"a) Bank loans\",\n    \"row 4\": \"The Port Authority had two credit facilities, one for $15,000 and the other for $5,000, with a major\",\n    \"row 5\": \"financial institution used to finance repairs and improvements related to access to the Billy Bishop\",\n    \"row 6\": \"Toronto City Airport.\",\n    \"row 7\": \"The original $15,000 facility was used for airport improvements including a ferry (\\u201cM/V David\",\n    \"row 8\": \"Hornell\\u2019), repairs to docking facilities and two new Ferry Passenger Transfer Facilities. On\",\n    \"row 9\": \"January 1, 2007, $11,250 of the original facility was converted to a 5 year fixed rate term. The fixed\",\n    \"row 10\": \"rate of 5.585% was obtained through a 15 year interest rate swap commencing on January 1, 2007,\",\n    \"row 11\": \"including a credit spread of 50 basis points, with a 20 year amortization period. On December 31,\",\n    \"row 12\": \"2012, the fair value of the swap was $1,719, (December 31, 2011: $2,027). The remaining $3,750 of\",\n    \"row 13\": \"the original credit facility was converted to a variable rate term loan on September 1, 2007 and\",\n    \"row 14\": \"bears interest at the bankers\\u2019 acceptance rate plus 0.5% or BMO prime rate. The term of the Loan\",\n    \"row 15\": \"was 5 years, with a 20 year amortization period. Prior to January 1, 2007, no principal was paid on\",\n    \"row 16\": \"this portion of the loan. The variable rate term loan matured in September 2012 and was extended\",\n    \"row 17\": \"for another 5 years on existing terms.\",\n    \"row 18\": \"An amount of $4,815 of the available $5,000 Credit Facility was drawn to finance the purchase of a\",\n    \"row 19\": \"second larger ferry (\\u201cM/V Marilyn Bell I\\u201d). The M/V Marilyn Bell  has a capacity of 200 passengers.\",\n    \"row 20\": \"The M/V Marilyn Bell  went into service on January 21, 2010. The M/V David Hornell, which was\",\n    \"row 21\": \"the original ferry in 2006, is now the back-up ferry for the Airport. The facility included interest at the\",\n    \"row 22\": \"bankers\\u2019 acceptance rate plus 2.0% or BMO prime rate plus 1.0%. The term of the Loan was\",\n    \"row 23\": \"5 years, with a 15 year amortization period. On October 4, 2012, this loan was repaid (2011 -\",\n    \"row 24\": \"$4,280).\",\n    \"row 25\": \"Principal payments for the $15,000 facility for the next five years are as follows:\",\n    \"row 26\": \"Year Fixed Variable Total\",\n    \"row 27\": \"$ $ $\",\n    \"row 28\": \"2013 487 188 675\",\n    \"row 29\": \"2014 475 188 663\",\n    \"row 30\": \"2015 500 188 688\",\n    \"row 31\": \"2016 526 188 714\",\n    \"row 32\": \"2017 553 188 141\",\n    \"row 33\": \"Thereafter 6,469 1,810 8,279\",\n    \"row 34\": \"9,010 2,750 11,760\",\n    \"row 35\": \"Less: current portion 487 188 675\",\n    \"row 36\": \"Long term 8.523 2,562 11,085\",\n    \"row 37\": \"b) Derivative instrument and hedge accounting\",\n    \"row 38\": \"On January 31, 2012, the Port Authority designated the interest rate swap in a hedging relationship\",\n    \"row 39\": \"with the $11,250 credit facility. Prospective and retrospective hedge effectiveness is assessed on\",\n    \"row 40\": \"these hedges using a hypothetical derivative method. The hypothetical derivative assessment\",\n    \"row 41\": \"involves comparing the effect of changes in interest rates each period on the changes in fair value\",\n    \"row 42\": \"of both the actual and hypothetical derivative. The effective portion of the interest rate swap is\",\n    \"row 43\": \"recorded in other comprehensive income until the forecasted transaction occurs. Where applicable,\",\n    \"row 44\": \"the fair value of the derivative has been adjusted to account for the Port Authority\\u2019s credit risk.\",\n    \"row 45\": \"Page 27\"\n}"